    "In particular, if encouragement is relatively costless (κ is low), product demand is elastic (ϵ is high), workers are relatively homogeneous in their individual chatbot productivity (γ is low), and chatbots offer large productivity gains (α b is high) but are costly to adopt (α c is high), then employer encouragement will tend to reduce workplace employment.",
    "Workplace wage bills.",
    "Encouraged firms increase their wage bills by:",
    "The prediction that employer encouragement unambiguously raises wage bills is a consequence of modeling AI chatbots solely as tools that augment worker productivity (see Equation (13)).",
    "As discussed in Section A.2.1, this result breaks for more general production technologies."
